name: Reject modernism, Embrace the Void
tweet: Felony murder, therefore, affects the charges available to prosecutors, but not necessarily the pool of potential defendants.  That is conspiracy liability, or aiding & abetting liability.

name: Reject modernism, Embrace the Void
tweet: As a defense lawyer, I believe that felony murder is overused. Prosecutors use felony murder (and thus a death penalty) as leverage to finagle pleas to robbery and manslaughter.

name: Reject modernism, Embrace the Void
tweet: The felony murder rule is therefore a rule that gets around *causation*. The felonious act need not necessarily *cause the death* as long as the death is a consequence of the felonious act.

name: Reject modernism, Embrace the Void
tweet: The felony murder rule is a common law rule that says any death that occurs in the commission of a felony is automatically murder.  Try to rob someone and they crack their skull trying to run away? Murder, even if the robber didn't touch him.
